OL,3,CDouble-amputee Ghurka veteran receives
OL,4,CMBE
OL,6,FA Gurkha veteran who lost both legs
OL,7,Fserving in Afghanistan has been made
OL,8,Fan MBE, recognising his "lifetime
OL,9,Fmission" to change perceptions of
OL,10,Fpeople with disabilities.
OL,12,FHari Budha Magar, who lives in
OL,13,FCanterbury, Kent, became the first
OL,14,Fdouble above-the-knee amputee (DAK) to
OL,15,Freach the summit of Mount Everest at
OL,16,F8,849m in 2023.
OL,18,FThe 44-year-old has been made a Member
OL,19,Fof the Order of the British Empire
OL,20,F(MBE) in the King's Birthday Honours
OL,21,Ffor services to disability awareness.
